### Describe the bug

@AroundInvoke not invoked on a classic resteasy endpoint in v 2.3.0.Final
Works fine in 2.2.3.Final

https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187030-users/topic/.40AroundInvoke.20not.20invoked.20on.20a.20classic.20resteasy.20endpoint.20in

### Expected behavior

@AroundInvoke is invoked on a classic resteasy endpoint

### Actual behavior

@AroundInvoke is NOT invoked on a classic resteasy endpoint

### How to Reproduce?

It can be verified by adding an interception to the guide, and apply it to the interface:
@ErrorHandlerClient
CountriesService

```java
@ErrorHandlerClient
@Priority(0)
@Interceptor
public class ErrorHandlerClientImpl {

    @AroundInvoke
    Object logInvocation(InvocationContext ctx) throws Exception {

        System.out.println("############### NEVER INVOKED FOR QUARKUS v 2.3.0.Final, but OK for 2.2.3.Final");
        return ctx.proceed();
    }
}
```

https://quarkus.io/guides/rest-client

And invoke the service: http://localhost:8080/country/name/greece

Note:
https://restcountries.eu/rest has changed to:
http://api.countrylayer.com
and require an access_key:
https://countrylayer.com/documentation/


